 BY FOLASHADE SHIYANBOLA YABA College of Technology, Lagos, will, on Monday, 22nd March 2021, resume normal academic activities. The Academic Board of the institution, at its meeting on Thursday, March 18, 2021, considered and approved that the College should resume normal academic activities immediately. This was disclosed in a statement signed by the Deputy Registrar, Academic Board of the institution, Mrs. Modupeola Osidipe. According to her, all staff and students are to ensure full compliance with all health authorities’ directives to contain the spread of COVID-19. “All are enjoined to ensure physical distancing, washing of hands, use of hand sanitizers, wearing of face masks and observance of other safety precautions,” she added. 